<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="576" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,978,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,978,1003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zetterstedt, 1846" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1846" box="[572,965,978,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Phaonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cincta">
<emphasis box="[572,745,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Phaonia cincta</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt, 
<number box="[900,957,978,1003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="1846.0">1846</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
with long plumose arista, 
<number box="[1274,1288,979,1003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="4.0">4</number>
dorsocentral setae, colour of body, short prealar seta, distinct acrostichal setae. The new species can be distinguished as follows: eye sparsely short haired, palpus dull yellow, antenna brownish-dark, legs brownish-yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="576" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,978,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1086,1111]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is based on the Latin name of the genus of tree in the hollow of which the larva of this species was found, 
<taxonomicName box="[446,533,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Phaonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juglans" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[446,533,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Juglans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
