<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="577" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,978,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,487,1230,1255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
Description. Male. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[425,487,1230,1255]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Head</emphasis>
</emphasis>
: Ground-colour black. Eye sparsely short haired. Fronto-orbital plates separated by a narrow frontal vitta which is 
<number box="[476,511,1266,1291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as wide as diameter of anterior ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1097,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,447,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,447,1923]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phaonia juglans sp. nov., male (holotype): A, Head, lateral view. B, Head and scutum, anterior view. C, Abdomen and scutellum, dorsal view. D, Sternite 5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253616/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
Fig. 
<number box="[1083,1097,1267,1291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Face, fronto-orbital plates, frontal vitta densely silvery pruinose, shining. Occiput light grey. Fronto-orbital plates with 
<number box="[1201,1215,1302,1327]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="6.0">6</number>
pair of strong long frontal setae in lower half and 
<number box="[490,504,1339,1363]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of very short hairs in upper half (
<figureCitation box="[937,1003,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,447,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,447,1923]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phaonia juglans sp. nov., male (holotype): A, Head, lateral view. B, Head and scutum, anterior view. C, Abdomen and scutellum, dorsal view. D, Sternite 5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253616/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
Fig. 
<number box="[989,1003,1339,1363]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Distance between eyes about equal to width of postpedicel. In lateral view, facial edge not projecting forward beyond the level of profrons. Antenna dark brownish; scape and pedicel brownish-yellow, postpedicel black except reddish base; arista long plumose, longest aristal hairs as long as diameter of postpedicel. Postpedicel ca 
<number box="[939,974,1446,1471]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as wide. Parafacial at level of insertion of arista narrower then width of postpedicel. Gena broad, depth below lowest eye-margin equal to 
<number box="[1422,1436,1483,1507]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="2.0">2</number>
times as diameter of postpedicel. Palpus dull yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,978,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,284,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Thorax</emphasis>
: Ground-colour black with thick greyish-white dust. Scutum with 
<number box="[1049,1063,1555,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="4.0">4</number>
distinct dark longitudinal vittae, seen from behind. Prosternum bare. Prealar seta short, half as long as posterior notopleural seta. Dorsocentrals 
<number box="[1385,1400,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1417,1432,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="4.0">4</number>
. Presutural acrostichals strong, 
<number box="[497,511,1627,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="2.0">2</number>
or 
<number box="[549,563,1627,1651]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="3.0">3</number>
pairs (assymetrical specimen), half as long as first pair of dorsocentrals (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,447,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,447,1923]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phaonia juglans sp. nov., male (holotype): A, Head, lateral view. B, Head and scutum, anterior view. C, Abdomen and scutellum, dorsal view. D, Sternite 5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253616/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,165,1663,1687]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Meron and katepimeron bare. Notopleuron bare. Katepisternal setae 
<number box="[980,991,1663,1687]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1010,1027,1663,1687]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="2.0">2</number>
. Scutellum grey dust, with undusted median line, without yellow marks, entirely bare on underside.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,978,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Wing</emphasis>
: Clear except for some light clouding over crossveins r-m and dm-cu, white at base. Cross-vein dm-cu upright, almost forming a right-angle with vein M but sinuous. Basicosta and tegula grey. Without costal spine. Radial node on lower side bare. Calypters white. Haltere yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,978,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,253,1843,1866]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Legs</emphasis>
: Coxae grey dusted. Fore femur brown, mid and hind femora yellow with brown dorsal stripe, all tibiae yellow, fore tarsomeres yellow, mid and hind tarsomeres brown. Fore tibia with one posterior seta. Mid tibia with only 
<number box="[216,230,1915,1939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="2.0">2</number>
posterior setae. 
<collectingCountry box="[438,494,1914,1939]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur without elongated posteroventrals but with a row of short setulae on posteroventral surface. 
<collectingCountry box="[422,478,1950,1975]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="576">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia without apical posteroventrals, with 
<number box="[980,994,1951,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="2.0">2</number>
anterodorsals, 
<number box="[1174,1188,1951,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="3.0">3</number>
anteroventrals and 
<number box="[1422,1436,1951,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="576" value="1.0">1</number>
posterodorsal seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="577">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Oval, elongate; dull yellow, with a dark median line. Tergites 
<number box="[1025,1039,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577" value="4.0">4</number>
and 
<number box="[1095,1109,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577" value="5.0">5</number>
grey dusted, tergites 
<number box="[1352,1366,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[1422,1436,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577" value="4.0">4</number>
with dark lateral marks at lower angles of tergites (
<figureCitation box="[721,787,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,447,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,447,1923]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phaonia juglans sp. nov., male (holotype): A, Head, lateral view. B, Head and scutum, anterior view. C, Abdomen and scutellum, dorsal view. D, Sternite 5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253616/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="577">
Fig. 
<number box="[773,787,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Sternite 
<number box="[923,937,188,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577" value="5.0">5</number>
as in figure 
<number box="[1077,1091,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577" value="3.0">3</number>
D.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="577">Terminalia</emphasis>
: Epandrium about as wide as high; surstylus elongate, longer than cerci in lateral view and bent medially with apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[489,558,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,199,1730]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[157,1429,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phaonia spp., male terminalia: A, B: Phaonia babarabica sp. nov. (holotype); C, D: Phaonia juglans sp. nov. (holotype). A, C, Terminalia, lateral view. B, D, Cercal plate, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253615/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="577">
Fig. 
<number box="[543,558,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C); cercal plate wider than high, without outer and inner ventral projections, with apex rectilinear in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[593,661,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1803,1825]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,199,1730]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[157,1429,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phaonia spp., male terminalia: A, B: Phaonia babarabica sp. nov. (holotype); C, D: Phaonia juglans sp. nov. (holotype). A, C, Terminalia, lateral view. B, D, Cercal plate, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253615/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="577">
Fig. 
<number box="[646,661,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,392]" box="[199,947,332,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="577">
